#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -Eeuo pipefail

cat <<'MSG'
llm-vm-kit commands

Daily use:
  ai-help                 show this command reference
  ai-status               inspect config, GPU, installed tools, and server state
  ai-chat [prompt]        chat with the selected local model
  ai-code [dir] [prompt]  run OpenCode against a project or prompt
  ai-agent [prompt]       run Hermes Agent with tools/browser support

Model config and serving:
  ai-model                show active model config and available presets
  ai-model mid-range      select Llama 3.3 70B GGUF, llama.cpp, 32K context
  ai-model max-power      select Hermes 3 Llama 3.1 405B, vLLM, 128K context
  ai-model MODEL          select a custom Hugging Face model
  ai-model MODEL --pull   select, download, and restart the selected model
  ai-pull                 download/start the backend selected in ai.env
  ai-server-start         start the selected backend
  ai-server-stop          stop managed local model servers
  ai-llama-start          start llama.cpp server directly
  ai-llama-stop           stop llama.cpp server directly
  ai-vllm-start           start vLLM server directly
  ai-vllm-stop            stop vLLM server directly
  ai-download-model       download/cache the configured llama.cpp GGUF model

Sync:
  ai-sync-from-server     pull projects, config, memory, outputs, and tool state
  ai-sync-to-server       push durable VM state back to dedicated storage
  ai-sync-status          dry-run push diff
  ai-sync-status pull     dry-run pull diff

Prompt and memory:
  set-system-prompt TEXT  set the shared chat system prompt
  set-system-prompt --show
  set-system-prompt --clear
  ai-set-system-prompt    alias for set-system-prompt
  ai-memory show          list manual shared memory
  ai-memory add TEXT      add a manual shared memory item
  ai-memory edit [N]      edit all memory or one numbered memory item
  ai-memory remove N      remove one memory item
  ai-memory clear         clear manual shared memory
  ai-memory path          print the active memory file path

Browser and maintenance:
  ai-browser-start        start headless Chrome/Chromium CDP for Hermes
  ai-browser-reset        reset the browser automation profile
  ai-configure            rewrite OpenCode/Hermes config from ai.env
  ai-backup               create a local archive of /workspace/ai and projects

Important files:
  /workspace/ai/ai.env
      active VM config
  /workspace/ai/persistent-config/ai.env.base
      synced base config copied to dedicated storage
  /workspace/ai/persistent-config/memory/active.md
      manual shared memory file
  /opt/llm-vm-kit/config/ai-sync.env
      VM-local dedicated-server sync settings

Typical fresh VM flow:
  cd /opt/llm-vm-kit
  bin/ai-sync-from-server
  bin/ai-model
  bash bootstrap.sh

Typical disposal flow:
  ai-sync-status to-server
  ai-sync-to-server
MSG
